# flyRank — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview

We are building **flyRank**, a full-stack web application.

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend:** React, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS
- **Backend:** Node.js

## TypeScript

- Enable and enforce **strict typing** at all times.
- Avoid `any`; prefer explicit types, interfaces, and generics.
- Type all component props, API responses, and shared utilities.
- Use type-safe patterns for state, routing, and data fetching.

## UI & Design

- Prioritize a **minimalist, premium tech** aesthetic.
- Favor clean layouts, generous whitespace, and restrained color palettes.
- Use Tailwind CSS consistently; avoid one-off inline styles unless necessary.
- Components should feel polished, responsive, and intentional — not cluttered.
- Prefer subtle motion and micro-interactions over heavy decoration.

## Code Quality

- Keep components small, focused, and reusable.
- Match existing project conventions before introducing new patterns.
- Write self-documenting code; add comments only for non-obvious logic.
- Minimize scope — solve the task at hand without over-engineering.

## Full-Stack Conventions

- Separate frontend and backend concerns clearly.
- Validate and type API contracts on both client and server.
- Never commit secrets; use environment variables for configuration.
